The '2013â14 UEFA Champions League' is the 59th season of Europe's premier club
football tournament organised by UEFA, and the 22nd season since it was renamed
from the European Champion Clubs' Cup to the UEFA Champions League.

The 2014 UEFA Champions League Final will be played at the EstÃ¡dio da Luz in
Lisbon, Portugal. Bayern Munich are the defending champions.

For the first time, the teams who qualify for the group stage will also qualify
for the newly formed 2013â14 UEFA Youth League, a competition available to
players aged 19 or under.
